A woman, believed to be in her 20s, was killed when she
was knocked over by a small bakkie on Friday morning. The accident occured at the North Rand and Rondebult Road
Intersection in Boksburg. ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene at 05:50 to find the
body of a woman, believed to be in her 20s, lying in the right-hand lane. "A small bakkie was parked a few metres in front of
her. ""Paramedics assessed the woman and found that
she had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. "CPR and advanced life support interventions were
immediately initiated, in an effort to revive the patient," said ER24
spokesman Russel Meiring. Unfortunately, after 30 minutes, no vital signs returned
and the woman was declared dead. The driver of the bakkie fortunately escaped injury. Local authorities were on the scene for further
investigations.